						<summary>

						<p>On a stone planted to the south of the Virabhadra temple in the village.</p>						

						<p>This is dated Śaka 1198, • • • • • Bhādrapada, ba. 10, Friday.</p>						

						<p>Records the gift of cows for burning a perpetual lamp to the temple of Kālēśvara by Kālāri Nate • • • • ., son of Chevvi-Seṭṭi and Mārasāni of Kāḷēśvara.</p>						

